Devastating floods and other catastrophic events brought about by global warming have convinced investors in China to back technology-focused solutions to bolstering food security. 

In April 2021, more than 7 billion yuan have been raised alone from venture funds for projects that develop everything from drones that spray crops with precise amounts of treatments to apps that digitise, streamline and increase the import of beef.

Today we commenced the distribution of the disinfectant kits to 5,750 families in Ja Ela and Wattala. 

Due to the current Covid situation in the area, we are not allowed to reach each family and the distribution takes place smoothly through the Village Child Development Committees.

Here are some pictures from the few locations we were permitted to visit.

Once again, a big thank you to the International Medical Health Organisation (IMHO) for their generous and timely contribution to support 1,300 of these families.
